<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Configs>
    <Section Label="General">
        <Config Label="Title Prefix" Variable="TITLEPREFIX" Type="string">
            <Comment>
                <Line>Added at the beginning of the &lt;title&gt; tag.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Title Suffix" Variable="TITLESUFFIX" Type="string">
            <Example>" - My University"</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Added at the end of the &lt;title&gt; tag.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Language" Variable="LANGUAGE" Type="string" Required="true">
            <Default>en</Default>
            <Example>en, de</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Language used (refers to language file in directory /languages)</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    </Section>
    <Section Label="Database">
    	<Config Label="Database Connection String" Variable="DATABASE" Type="string" Required="true">
        	<Example>mysql://vtcal:abc123@localhost/vtcalendar</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>This is the database connection string used by the PEAR library.</Line>
                <Line>It has the format: "mysql://user:password@host/databasename" or "postgres://user:password@host/databasename"</Line>
            </Comment>
    	</Config>
        <Config Label="SQL Log File" Variable="SQLLOGFILE" Type="string">
            <Example>/var/log/vtcalendarsql.log</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Put a name of a (folder and) file where the calendar logs every SQL query to the database.</Line>
                <Line>This is good for debugging but make sure you write into a file that's not readable by the webserver or else you may expose private information.</Line>
                <Line>If left blank ("") no log will be kept. That's the default.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    </Section>
    <Section Label="Authentication">
    	<Config Label="User ID Regular Expression" Variable="REGEXVALIDUSERID" Type="string" Required="true">
            <Default>/^[A-Za-z][\._A-Za-z0-9\-\\]{1,49}$/</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>This regular expression defines what is considered a valid user-ID.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Database Authentication" Variable="AUTH_DB" Type="boolean">
            <Default>true</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Authenticate users against the database.</Line>
                <Line>If enabled, this is always performed before any other authentication.</Line>
            </Comment>
            <Dependants>
                <Config Label="Prefix for Database Usernames" Variable="AUTH_DB_USER_PREFIX" Type="string">
                    <Example>db_</Example>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>This prefix is used when creating/editing a local user-ID (in the DB "user" table), e.g. "calendar."</Line>
                        <Line>If you only use auth_db just leave it an empty string.</Line>
                        <Line>Its purpose is to avoid name-space conflicts with the users authenticated via LDAP or HTTP.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
                <Config Label="Database Authentication Notice" Variable="AUTH_DB_NOTICE" Type="string">
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>This displays a text (or nothing) on the Update tab behind the user user management options.</Line>
                        <Line>It could be used if you employ both, AUTH_DB and AUTH_LDAP at the same time to let users know that they should create local users only if they are not in the LDAP.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
                <Config Label="Create Main Admin Account" Variable="AUTH_DB_CREATEADMIN" Type="boolean" IsDefinition="false">
                    <Default>true</Default>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>If the database has not yet been populated, you will need to create a main admin account in order to administer the calendar.</Line>
                        <Line>However, if you are using LDAP or HTTP authentication this will not be necessary assuming you specify main admin account names under those sections.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                    <Dependants>
                        <Config Label="Main Admin Username" Variable="AUTH_DB_CREATEADMIN_USERNAME" Type="string" Required="true" IsDefinition="false">
                            <Example>root</Example>
                        </Config>
                        <Config Label="Main Admin Password" Variable="AUTH_DB_CREATEADMIN_PASSWORD" Type="string" Required="true" IsDefinition="false"/>
                    </Dependants>
                </Config>
            </Dependants>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="LDAP Authentication" Variable="AUTH_LDAP" Type="boolean">
            <Default>false</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Authenticate users against a LDAP server.</Line>
                <Line>If enabled, HTTP authenticate will be ignored.</Line>
            </Comment>
            <Dependants>
            	<Config Label="LDAP Host Name" Variable="LDAP_HOST" Type="string" Required="true">
            	    <Example>directory.myuniversity.edu or ldap://directory.myuniversity.edu/ or ldaps://secure-directory.myuniversity.edu/</Example>
            	    <Comment>
            	        <Line>If you are using OpenLDAP 2.x.x you can specify a URL ('ldap://host/') instead of the hostname ('host').</Line>
            	    </Comment>
            	</Config>
                <Config Label="LDAP Port" Variable="LDAP_PORT" Type="number">
                    <Default>389</Default>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>The port to connect to. Ignored if LDAP Host Name is a URL.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
            	<Config Label="LDAP Username Attribute" Variable="LDAP_USERFIELD" Type="string" Required="true">
                    <Example>sAMAccountName</Example>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>The attribute which contains the username.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
            	<Config Label="LDAP Base DN" Variable="LDAP_BASE_DN" Type="string" Required="true">
                    <Example>DC=myuniversity,DC=edu</Example>
                </Config>
                <Config Label="Additional LDAP Search Filter" Variable="LDAP_SEARCH_FILTER" Type="string">
                    <Example>(objectClass=person)</Example>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>An optional filter to add to the LDAP search.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
                <Config Label="LDAP Search Bind Username." Variable="LDAP_BIND_USER" Type="string">
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>Before authenticating the user, we first check if the username exists.</Line>
                        <Line>If your LDAP server does not allow anonymous connections, specific a username here.</Line>
                        <Line>Leave this blank to connect anonymously.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
                <Config Label="LDAP Search Bind Password" Variable="LDAP_BIND_PASSWORD" Type="string">
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>Before authenticating the user, we first check if the username exists.</Line>
                        <Line>If your LDAP server does not allow anonymous connections, specific a password here.</Line>
                        <Line>Leave this blank to connect anonymously.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
                <Config Label="Accounts to Add as Main Admins" Variable="LDAP_MAINADMINS" Type="string" IsDefinition="false">
                    <Example>bsmith;ajackson</Example>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>A semi-colon (;) delimited list of account names that will be added as main admins.</Line>
                        <Line>No DB accounts will be created for these account names.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
            </Dependants>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="HTTP Authentication" Variable="AUTH_HTTP" Type="boolean">
            <Default>false</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Authenticate users by sending an HTTP request to a server.</Line>
                <Line>A HTTP status code of 200 will authorize the user. Otherwise, they will not be authorized.</Line>
                <Line>If LDAP authentication is enabled, this will be ignored.</Line>
            </Comment>
            <Dependants>
            	<Config Label="HTTP Authorizaton URL" Variable="AUTH_HTTP_URL" Type="string" Required="true">
                    <Example>http://localhost/customauth.php</Example>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>The URL to use for the BASIC HTTP Authentication.</Line>
                    </Comment>
            	</Config>
                <Config Label="Accounts to Add as Main Admins" Variable="AUTH_HTTP_MAINADMINS" Type="string" IsDefinition="false">
                    <Example>bsmith;ajackson</Example>
                    <Comment>
                        <Line>A semi-colon (;) delimited list of account names that will be added as main admins.</Line>
                        <Line>No DB accounts will be created for these account names.</Line>
                    </Comment>
                </Config>
            </Dependants>
        </Config>
    </Section>
    <Section Label="Cookies">
        <Config Label="Cookie Path" Variable="BASEPATH" Type="string">
            <Example>/calendar/</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>If you are hosting more than one VTCalendar on your server, you may want to set this to this calendar's path.</Line>
                <Line>Otherwise, the cookie will be submitted with a default path.</Line>
                <Line>This must start and end with a forward slash (/), unless the it is exactly "/".</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Cookie Host Name" Variable="BASEDOMAIN" Type="string">
            <Example>localhost</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>If you are hosting more than one VTCalendar on your server, you may want to set this to your server's host name.</Line>
                <Line>Otherwise, the cookie will be submitted with a default host name.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    </Section>
    <Section Label="URL">
    	<Config Label="Calendar Base URL" Variable="BASEURL" Type="string" Required="true">
            <Example>http://localhost/calendar/</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>This is the absolute URL where your calendar software is located.</Line>
                <Line>This MUST end with a slash "/"</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Secure Calendar Base URL" Variable="SECUREBASEURL" Type="string">
        	<Default Internal="BASEURL"></Default>
            <Example>https://localhost/calendar/</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>This is the absolute path where the secure version of the calendar is located.</Line>
                <Line>If you are not using URL, set this to the same address as BASEURL.</Line>
                <Line>This MUST end with a slash "/"</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    </Section>
    <Section Label="Date/Time">
    	<Config Label="Timezone Offset" Variable="TIMEZONE_OFFSET" Type="number" Required="true">
            <Default>5</Default>
            <Example>-5</Example>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Defines the offset to GMT, can be positive or negative</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    	<Config Label="Week Starting Day" Variable="WEEK_STARTING_DAY" Type="number" Required="true">
            <Default>0</Default>
    	    <Choices>
    	        <Choice Value="0">Sunday (0)</Choice>
    	        <Choice Value="1">Monday (1)</Choice>
    	    </Choices>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Defines the week starting day</Line>
                <Line Hidden="true">Allowable values - 0 for "Sunday" or 1 for "Monday"</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Use AM/PM" Variable="USE_AMPM" Type="boolean">
            <Default>true</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Defines time format e.g. 1am-11pm (true) or 1:00-23:00 (false)</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    </Section>
    <Section Label="Display">
    	<Config Label="Column Position" Variable="COLUMNSIDE" Type="string" Required="true">
            <Default>RIGHT</Default>
    	    <Choices>
    	        <Choice>LEFT</Choice>
    	        <Choice>RIGHT</Choice>
    	    </Choices>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Which side the little calendar, 'jump to', 'today is', etc. will be on.</Line>
                <Line>RIGHT is more user friendly for users with low resolutions.</Line>
                <Line Hidden="true">Values must be LEFT or RIGHT.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Show Upcoming Tab" Variable="SHOW_UPCOMING_TAB" Type="boolean">
            <Default>true</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Whether or not the upcoming tab will be shown.</Line>
            </Comment>
        	<Dependants>
        		<Config Label="Max Upcoming Events" Variable="MAX_UPCOMING_EVENTS" Type="number" Required="true">
        			<Default>75</Default>
        			<Comment>
        				<Line>The maximum number of upcoming events displayed.</Line>
        			</Comment>
        		</Config>
        	</Dependants>
        </Config>
        <Config Label="Show Month Overlap" Variable="SHOW_MONTH_OVERLAP" Type="boolean">
            <Default>true</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Whether or not events in month view on days that are not actually part of the current month should be shown.</Line>
                <Line>For example, if the first day of the month starts on a Wednesday, then Sunday-Tuesday are from the previous month.</Line>
                <Line>Values must be true or false.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    </Section>
    <Section Label="Cache">
    	<Config Label="HTTP Authentication Cache" Variable="AUTH_HTTP_CACHE" Type="boolean">
    		<Default>false</Default>
    		<Comment>
    			<Line>Cache successful HTTP authentication attempts as hashes in DB.</Line>
    			<Line>This acts as a failover if the HTTP authentication fails due to a server error.</Line>
    		</Comment>
    		<Dependants>
    			<Config Label="HTTP Authentication Cache Expiration" Variable="AUTH_HTTP_CACHE_EXPIRATIONDAYS" Type="number" Required="true">
    				<Default>4</Default>
    				<Comment>
    					<Line>The number of days in which data in the HTTP authentication cache is valid.</Line>
    				</Comment>
    			</Config>
    		</Dependants>
    	</Config>
    	<Config Label="Max Category Name Cache Size" Variable="MAX_CACHESIZE_CATEGORYNAME" Type="number" Required="true">
            <Default>100</Default>
            <Comment>
                <Line>Cache the list of category names in memory if the calendar has less than or equal to this number.</Line>
            </Comment>
        </Config>
    </Section>
</Configs>